WEBVTT

00:02.750 --> 00:04.210
[ Singing in Italian ]

00:04.210 --> 00:05.620
[ Plays discordant note ]

00:07.380 --> 00:08.710
Zola!

00:08.710 --> 00:11.080
[ Strumming guitar ]

00:11.080 --> 00:13.880
Meredith:
In your first year
as an attending surgeon...

00:13.880 --> 00:15.620
[ Singing continues ]

00:15.620 --> 00:17.500
...you're told
to take baby steps.

00:17.500 --> 00:22.170
[ Singing continues ]

00:22.170 --> 00:25.580
Look for the easy cases,
the sure wins.

00:25.580 --> 00:27.830
Hey. Come on.

00:27.830 --> 00:29.670
Is it hard to learn
to play guitar?

00:29.670 --> 00:31.210
Apparently, yes.

00:31.210 --> 00:32.750
No sense of making
an ass of yourself.

00:32.750 --> 00:34.120
I can't understand
what he's singing.

00:34.120 --> 00:36.080
And let's be thankful
for that.

00:36.080 --> 00:37.790
Better to rack up
some easy victories.

00:37.790 --> 00:39.380
Mom, your trophies.

00:39.380 --> 00:40.380
Are you bringing them
for show and tell?

00:40.380 --> 00:42.000
No. Show and tell is when
you're proud of something.

00:42.000 --> 00:44.580
This is more like...

00:44.580 --> 00:46.000
if Mommy bought milk,
and it was spoiled,

00:46.000 --> 00:48.620
and I have to return it.

00:48.620 --> 00:50.420
[ Plays discordant note ]

00:50.420 --> 00:52.620
[ Singing continues ]

00:55.170 --> 00:56.500
[ Strumming, singing stops ]

00:56.500 --> 00:58.500
Andrew,
I'm going to work.

00:58.500 --> 01:00.080
At the hospital.

01:00.080 --> 01:02.540
Remember, the big building with
a lot of sick people inside?

01:02.540 --> 01:03.920
Would you like to come?
-I already called in sick.

01:03.920 --> 01:05.170
You know
you're not sick.

01:05.170 --> 01:06.670
My whole body just --
it hurts, okay?

01:06.670 --> 01:08.500
I'm sick.

01:08.500 --> 01:12.250
How come Maggie's friend never
has to take a bath and we do?

01:12.250 --> 01:15.170
Because he's European.

01:15.170 --> 01:17.420
Would you go get your brother
and sister, please?

01:17.420 --> 01:19.790
[ The Great Escape's
"I Can't Resist" plays ]

01:19.790 --> 01:22.460
You can't avoid bad outcomes
for your whole career,

01:22.460 --> 01:24.460
but you can sure try.

01:24.460 --> 01:26.670
♪♪

01:26.670 --> 01:28.210
[ Screams ]

01:28.210 --> 01:29.250
[ Screams, laughs ]

01:29.250 --> 01:32.040
♪♪

01:34.380 --> 01:38.960
♪♪

01:38.960 --> 01:41.790
♪ Hey, what you got
in the shop for me? ♪

01:41.790 --> 01:44.170
♪ Hey, silver lining
just in time for tea ♪

01:44.170 --> 01:46.540
♪ Hey, chaos touch me ♪

01:46.540 --> 01:49.000
♪ Seductively soothing
my intensity ♪

01:49.000 --> 01:51.460
♪ Hey, I'm jumping ship
and not giving up ♪

01:51.460 --> 01:53.670
Excuse me.
Do you work here?

01:53.670 --> 01:54.670
Yes, I do.

01:54.670 --> 01:56.080
Oh, great.

01:56.080 --> 01:57.540
Can you respond to this
morning's harassment allegations

01:57.540 --> 01:59.080
by the radiologist
in Phoenix?

01:59.080 --> 02:01.080
She claims Harper Avery
shoved her up against a --

02:01.080 --> 02:02.620
How does it feel to be working
under the name

02:02.620 --> 02:04.460
of an alleged
sexual predator?

02:04.460 --> 02:05.960
Are those
Harper Avery Awards?

02:05.960 --> 02:06.750
What are you doing
with them?

02:06.750 --> 02:07.960
I'm returning them.

02:07.960 --> 02:09.420
Excuse me.

02:09.420 --> 02:10.420
[ Indistinct questions ]

02:10.420 --> 02:11.620
Excuse me.
Excuse me.

02:11.620 --> 02:12.880
'Cause getting
a bad reputation....

02:12.880 --> 02:14.380
Excuse me.

02:14.380 --> 02:15.920
...can finish you
before you start.

02:15.920 --> 02:17.540
♪♪

02:17.540 --> 02:19.380
Hey, I'm pulling the plug
on your contest.

02:19.380 --> 02:20.500
I'm killing it.

02:20.500 --> 02:21.830
What do you want me to do
with the $100 million?

02:21.830 --> 02:23.170
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.

02:23.170 --> 02:26.120
No, no. If word gets out
that Harper Avery's grandson

02:26.120 --> 02:28.830
secretly funded a competition
that he entered himself?

02:28.830 --> 02:30.540
Well, that's just gonna mean
more nasty headlines

02:30.540 --> 02:31.920
that we do not need
right now.

02:31.920 --> 02:34.710
Dr. Bai--

02:34.710 --> 02:36.500
You funded the contest?

02:36.500 --> 02:40.040
♪♪

02:40.040 --> 02:41.250
You knew, didn't you?

02:41.250 --> 02:42.620
I beg your pardon?

02:42.620 --> 02:43.620
Of course you knew.
You had to know.

02:43.620 --> 02:44.960
You made up the rules.
[ Scoffs ]

02:44.960 --> 02:46.670
"Rules."
What a crock.

02:46.670 --> 02:49.120
Look, I really have no idea
what you're talking about.

02:49.120 --> 02:50.380
I am not a cheater.

02:50.380 --> 02:53.330
I have never cheated
on anything in my life.

02:53.330 --> 02:55.790
Um, why are you
telling me this?

02:55.790 --> 02:57.960
[ Hushed voice ] I know Jackson
put up the money for the contest

02:57.960 --> 02:59.580
and asked you to judge.

02:59.580 --> 03:00.960
Wait. Wait.

03:00.960 --> 03:03.670
[ Hushed voice ] Jackson put up
the money for the contest?

03:03.670 --> 03:04.830
Who asked you
to judge?

03:07.540 --> 03:08.880
Slimy!

03:08.880 --> 03:11.750
That's what it was.
It was slimy.

03:11.750 --> 03:12.920
Come again, now?

03:12.920 --> 03:15.670
You set me up to make it
look like I'm in cahoots

03:15.670 --> 03:16.830
with my ex-husband?

03:16.830 --> 03:18.580
That is -- That is low.

03:18.580 --> 03:20.210
What the hell are you
talking about?

03:20.210 --> 03:21.920
I'm talking about
you duping me

03:21.920 --> 03:23.710
into a phony
director position

03:23.710 --> 03:27.000
where I unwittingly decide
who wins the prize money

03:27.000 --> 03:29.000
that my ex-husband
put up

03:29.000 --> 03:30.620
so that I look slimy.

03:30.620 --> 03:33.250
Because you are!
Slimy!

03:33.250 --> 03:34.380
All due respect!

03:36.420 --> 03:41.460
♪♪

03:41.460 --> 03:46.540
♪♪

03:46.540 --> 03:48.380
Mom, we need to talk
about this contest.

03:48.380 --> 03:49.540
Honey, come in.
I want you to meet --

03:49.540 --> 03:51.420
Erin Mason,
crisis management.

03:51.420 --> 03:53.000
You're just the man
I was looking for.

03:53.000 --> 03:54.750
And he sure is camera-friendly.
That doesn't hurt us.

03:54.750 --> 03:56.420
[ Exhales sharply ]

03:56.420 --> 03:58.000
You assured me you and I could
handle this together.

03:58.000 --> 04:00.330
Dr. Avery, if I had
an aggressive cancer,

04:00.330 --> 04:01.960
would you recommend
I operate on myself

04:01.960 --> 04:03.330
or hire a professional?

04:03.330 --> 04:05.120
Sweetheart,
this is what Erin does.

04:05.120 --> 04:06.210
Let's hear her out.

04:06.210 --> 04:08.420
That lawsuit brought by
the 13 women

04:08.420 --> 04:10.670
who signed and then violated
their NDAs?

04:10.670 --> 04:11.960
It's tip of the iceberg.

04:11.960 --> 04:13.710
This is a
developing situation,

04:13.710 --> 04:16.170
and it's getting worse
by the minute.

04:16.170 --> 04:18.710
So, this is how you get out
from under the bad name

04:18.710 --> 04:20.330
of Harper Avery?

04:20.330 --> 04:22.380
With a surgical
innovation contest

04:22.380 --> 04:24.170
secretly funded
by his damn grandson?

04:24.170 --> 04:26.500
-What?
-And that's out. Okay.

04:26.500 --> 04:28.120
Wait. Jackson,
you're the anonymous donor?

04:28.120 --> 04:29.580
What's this now?

04:29.580 --> 04:31.620
You put up the money, and then
you entered the contest?

04:31.620 --> 04:33.620
You entered
your own contest?

04:33.620 --> 04:36.080
Oh, God. Is this some kind
of tax-evasion scheme?

04:36.080 --> 04:37.880
What? No. It's just me
trying to do some good.

04:37.880 --> 04:38.880
Anonymously.
That's it.

04:38.880 --> 04:40.170
Well, that didn't work.

04:40.170 --> 04:41.750
Public perception
is everything,

04:41.750 --> 04:44.170
and they're going to destroy you
if this gets out.

04:44.170 --> 04:46.040
Then, let's not
let it get out.

04:46.040 --> 04:49.670
Agreed. And to that end,
I have some good news.

04:49.670 --> 04:50.710
[ Clears throat ]

04:50.710 --> 04:52.460
You are welcome.

04:52.460 --> 04:54.460
What's this?

04:54.460 --> 04:56.710
It is a distraction
for the press.

04:56.710 --> 04:59.080
I've been in touch with
the various medical charities,

04:59.080 --> 05:03.420
and Angels of Humanity
has a very high-profile
surgery for you.

05:03.420 --> 05:05.420
You want me to operate on
a child as a PR stunt?

05:05.420 --> 05:08.330
Are you kidding?
-No. I want you to heal a child.

05:08.330 --> 05:10.620
This patient
is arriving this morning,

05:10.620 --> 05:12.460
and we would like you to work
with Meredith Grey.

05:12.460 --> 05:14.620
Of course you would.
Maybe because she just
won a Harper Avery?

05:14.620 --> 05:17.880
No, because she's giving
hers back -- and her mother's.

05:17.880 --> 05:20.080
We're in a Category Five storm,
here.

05:20.080 --> 05:22.420
We need good press,
yesterday.

05:22.420 --> 05:24.290
Then, we are going to
go after these women.

05:24.290 --> 05:25.290
We are going to
attack their --

05:25.290 --> 05:26.460
No, no, no, no, no.

05:26.460 --> 05:28.080
You will not go after any
of these wom-- no.

05:28.080 --> 05:30.750
Listen, Boy Scouts
and Girl Scouts,

05:30.750 --> 05:34.500
someone is going down
for this.

05:34.500 --> 05:37.620
I have spent most of my adult
life building up the Avery name,

05:37.620 --> 05:40.040
and now
it's gonna take me down.

05:40.040 --> 05:43.210
I guess I could just go back
to being Catherine Fox.

05:43.210 --> 05:44.500
Jackson:
Oh, that's great, Mom.

05:44.500 --> 05:47.120
Thanks, from your Avery son
and granddaughter.

05:47.120 --> 05:49.250
Look, if it's a scapegoat
they want,

05:49.250 --> 05:50.670
I'm the one that signed
the settlements.

05:50.670 --> 05:51.790
Catherine.

05:51.790 --> 05:53.790
-I could live with that.
-Absolutely not.

05:53.790 --> 05:55.790
There's no way a powerful black
woman is gonna take the fall

05:55.790 --> 05:57.080
for a rich old
white guy

05:57.080 --> 05:58.620
that couldn't keep
his damn hands to himself. No.

05:58.620 --> 06:02.250
Jackson, I love your passion,
but this is not up to you.

06:02.250 --> 06:04.000
I'm still in charge
of this foundation.

06:04.000 --> 06:05.580
It's not your decision.

06:05.580 --> 06:07.460
Now go.
Meet your patient.

06:07.460 --> 06:09.120
[ Sighs ]

06:09.120 --> 06:10.330
[ Hushed conversation ]

06:10.330 --> 06:11.880
[ Hushed voice ] Hey.
You returned the awards?

06:11.880 --> 06:12.750
Is that really necessary?

06:12.750 --> 06:14.380
Yes, it was.

06:14.380 --> 06:16.170
You didn't want to give us
a heads up, Meredith?

06:16.170 --> 06:18.000
Did you really think
you were gonna get away

06:18.000 --> 06:19.380
with rigging the contest?

06:19.380 --> 06:21.790
No. How does the news
travel so fast?

06:21.790 --> 06:23.620
I didn't rig any contest.

06:23.620 --> 06:25.380
It's pretty ballsy.

06:25.380 --> 06:27.580
Were you gonna act like
you weren't gonna win,

06:27.580 --> 06:29.710
and then, at the minute,
just pull ahead and be like,

06:29.710 --> 06:31.420
"Hey, look, I won"?

06:31.420 --> 06:32.620
Right.
Are you joking,

06:32.620 --> 06:34.170
or do you really think
that's something I would do?

06:34.170 --> 06:35.670
I mean,
I don't know what to think.

06:35.670 --> 06:36.670
Do you care
to explain?

06:36.670 --> 06:38.290
I don't, no.

06:38.290 --> 06:41.120
I do need your help on a
craniofacial dysplasia excision.

06:41.120 --> 06:42.420
What do you say?
-A PR stunt?

06:42.420 --> 06:43.500
No, thanks.

06:43.500 --> 06:45.170
Whoa.

06:45.170 --> 06:46.170
Is that...

06:46.170 --> 06:48.960
♪♪

06:52.960 --> 06:55.710
I think that is
our patient.

06:55.710 --> 06:56.710
Are you sure
you don't want to help?

06:59.250 --> 07:02.080
What. Is there
something on my face?

07:02.080 --> 07:05.330
[ Nervous laughter ]

07:18.080 --> 07:19.040
Okay, Grassy Lane Farm?
Too pricey?

07:19.040 --> 07:20.500
No. I mean, if you like it,
let's do it.

07:20.500 --> 07:23.540
Okay,
the Old Piano Factory.

07:23.540 --> 07:26.120
There's this 3-tiered
pricing thingy.

07:26.120 --> 07:28.330
Old Piano Factory
is gorgeous,

07:28.330 --> 07:30.330
but you would --
you'd need a time machine.

07:30.330 --> 07:32.540
'Cause you'd have to go back
like six months

07:32.540 --> 07:34.330
to even think about booking it
for this year.

07:34.330 --> 07:35.750
But have you thought
about Magnolia's?

07:35.750 --> 07:37.420
Or Cloudland Inn?

07:37.420 --> 07:39.120
Ooh, ooh, ooh! Green Shutters.
Look that one up.

07:39.120 --> 07:40.960
Karev, Wilson,
what are you doing?

07:40.960 --> 07:43.920
Well, my surgery got cancelled
'cause of Handsy Avery.

07:43.920 --> 07:46.040
So, we are trying to plan
a wedding, but we suck at it.

07:46.040 --> 07:47.710
Yes! That's good.
Plan your wedding.

07:47.710 --> 07:49.040
Set the date.
Put it on the calendar.

07:49.040 --> 07:50.500
This place needs morale.

07:50.500 --> 07:54.580
This place needs some things
to feel good about

07:54.580 --> 07:56.120
and look forward to.

07:56.120 --> 07:58.670
Yeah, yeah,
lock that down.

07:58.670 --> 08:00.290
Great, now it's
a work thing.

08:00.290 --> 08:01.500
I'll do it.

08:01.500 --> 08:03.040
I mean,
I just lost my contest.

08:03.040 --> 08:05.920
I know I left my own wedding
at a pretty inopportune time,

08:05.920 --> 08:07.750
but prior to that,
I planned the hell out of it.

08:07.750 --> 08:08.790
If you need help,
I can do it.

08:08.790 --> 08:12.920
I just need a date
and a budget.

08:12.920 --> 08:14.500
Okay, we're doing that.

08:14.500 --> 08:16.540
[ Chuckling ] Really?
Yeah. We hate party planning.

08:16.540 --> 08:17.960
And if I promise not to
leave you at the altar,

08:17.960 --> 08:19.210
can we just
let her do it?

08:19.210 --> 08:20.170
I feel like
I just won the lottery.

08:20.170 --> 08:21.420
Okay.

08:21.420 --> 08:22.620
So, budget.

08:22.620 --> 08:24.880
Okay, this...

08:24.880 --> 08:26.290
This is what
I can kick in.

08:26.290 --> 08:27.830
Now you check
your account.

08:27.830 --> 08:34.620
♪♪

08:34.620 --> 08:35.540
What's wrong?

08:35.540 --> 08:37.210
Are you broke?

08:37.210 --> 08:40.040
Do I have to tell Beyoncé
that we can't afford her?

08:40.040 --> 08:41.670
Seriously, what's wrong?

08:41.670 --> 08:44.380
Did it just turn into,
like, a BYOB kind of thing?

08:44.380 --> 08:45.330
Can't do this
right now.

08:50.380 --> 08:54.960
[ Indistinct questions ]

08:54.960 --> 08:56.540
[ Exhales sharply ]

08:56.540 --> 08:57.880
Are you sure you don't want to
take him somewhere else?

08:57.880 --> 08:59.330
I mean, it's only
his 6-month checkup.

08:59.330 --> 09:00.830
No. Karev said
he'd do it.

09:00.830 --> 09:02.040
It's a perk,
so I'm taking it.

09:02.040 --> 09:04.120
Plus, the birth mom's
coming here.

09:04.120 --> 09:05.420
Right.

09:05.420 --> 09:06.920
And I still think it's weird
that she has the right

09:06.920 --> 09:08.790
to just show up at
his doctor's appointments.

09:08.790 --> 09:09.790
Owen,
you're fostering.

09:09.790 --> 09:10.790
You might not get
to adopt him.

09:10.790 --> 09:13.460
[ Sighs ] I know.

09:13.460 --> 09:15.790
I keep trying to think of it as,
like, a practice baby.

09:15.790 --> 09:17.880
But he is such a cute
practice baby.

09:17.880 --> 09:19.330
[ Laughs ]
-Okay.

09:19.330 --> 09:21.040
Now, protect him like
a football. Let's go.

09:21.040 --> 09:22.380
Okay.

09:22.380 --> 09:24.080
[ Car door closes ]

09:24.080 --> 09:26.620
[ Indistinct talking ]

09:26.620 --> 09:28.210
[ Indistinct questions ]

09:28.210 --> 09:30.210
No comment!
No comment!

09:30.210 --> 09:31.960
[ Elevator bell dings ]
Ooh! Hey!

09:31.960 --> 09:33.460
Oh, hey.

09:33.460 --> 09:34.750
You're so late.

09:34.750 --> 09:36.670
[ Sighs ]
Did you get stopped
by those reporters?

09:36.670 --> 09:39.960
No. I was dealing with a very
sad Sofia. Sobbing again.

09:39.960 --> 09:42.830
Refusing to go
to school.

09:42.830 --> 09:45.250
I mean, I just -- I had to
bribe her with snuggle time.

09:45.250 --> 09:47.540
And I promised her I would
stay home with her tomorrow.

09:47.540 --> 09:48.880
Poor thing,
she just hates school.

09:48.880 --> 09:50.210
And I don't...

09:50.210 --> 09:52.000
I don't know
what to do.

09:52.000 --> 09:54.960
That's too bad.

09:54.960 --> 09:59.120
Maybe you can bribe me with some
snuggle time after my consult.

09:59.120 --> 10:02.120
[ Elevator bell dings ]

10:02.120 --> 10:11.580
♪♪

10:11.580 --> 10:14.620
His parents
are loving people.

10:14.620 --> 10:16.960
They took him for a surgery
in Caracas,

10:16.960 --> 10:18.710
but no one
would touch it.

10:18.710 --> 10:21.210
And it kept growing.

10:21.210 --> 10:23.380
He's a great kid.

10:23.380 --> 10:24.790
Do you think you
can help him?

10:24.790 --> 10:26.250
We certainly hope so.

10:26.250 --> 10:28.580
[ Ringtone playing ]

10:28.580 --> 10:30.670
-Will you excuse me?
-Yeah, of course.

10:30.670 --> 10:32.290
Hello?

10:32.290 --> 10:34.670
In these old scans,
it's extending into the orbit

10:34.670 --> 10:36.120
and putting pressure
on his optic nerve

10:36.120 --> 10:37.540
Yeah.
That's definitely a concern.

10:37.540 --> 10:39.540
I'm also worried
about his airway.

10:39.540 --> 10:41.040
Helm, his head's
tilted a bit.

10:41.040 --> 10:42.000
Can you get in there
and readjust, please?

10:42.000 --> 10:43.040
Helm: Copy that.

10:47.120 --> 10:50.170
Just need
another angle...

10:50.170 --> 10:51.710
Oh, good.
This is my good side.

10:51.710 --> 10:52.920
[ Laughs ] Totally.

10:52.920 --> 10:55.250
[ Whirring ]

10:55.250 --> 10:56.920
I know what
you're thinking --

10:56.920 --> 10:58.710
good-looking and funny.

10:58.710 --> 10:59.920
Some people just have
all the luck.

10:59.920 --> 11:01.500
[ Chuckles ]

11:01.500 --> 11:04.960
[ Door opens, closes ]

11:04.960 --> 11:06.540
Thank you.

11:06.540 --> 11:08.920
Meredith: It's growing
deep into the retropharynx

11:08.920 --> 11:10.040
Which is why
I'm worried about

11:10.040 --> 11:11.460
him losing his ability
to speak...

11:11.460 --> 11:13.960
asphyxiating in his sleep.
I mean, look at this.

11:13.960 --> 11:16.540
It would be impossible
to excise that entire thing.

11:16.540 --> 11:18.040
I'm gonna have to just
contour it down

11:18.040 --> 11:20.080
to get the best
cosmetic outcome possible,

11:20.080 --> 11:21.750
preserving his breathing
and his sight.

11:21.750 --> 11:23.710
Meredith: No. We have to
do a total resection,

11:23.710 --> 11:25.080
pull the whole thing out.

11:25.080 --> 11:26.920
I mean, your way
avoids a bad outcome,

11:26.920 --> 11:28.540
but it doesn't solve
our problem.

11:28.540 --> 11:30.460
Yeah, well,
neither does killing him.

11:30.460 --> 11:31.670
Okay, sure,
you're right,

11:31.670 --> 11:33.120
he's gonna have to come back
for further resection.

11:33.120 --> 11:34.380
He lives in Venezuela.

11:34.380 --> 11:36.170
Which is why
they sent him here.

11:36.170 --> 11:38.830
We pull this off, he gets a
chance at having his life back.

11:38.830 --> 11:40.670
Plus, you and I know
we really can't afford

11:40.670 --> 11:43.210
a bad outcome
right now.

11:43.210 --> 11:44.580
Oh. Okay.

11:44.580 --> 11:45.830
Well, at least our motives
are clear.

11:45.830 --> 11:46.830
Come on, Mer.

11:46.830 --> 11:48.210
No, I get it --

11:48.210 --> 11:51.210
safe option, solid odds,
and glowing press.

11:51.210 --> 11:55.170
I'm sorry, Doctors,
we have a problem.

11:55.170 --> 11:56.920
I'm afraid we have to
cancel this surgery.

12:01.500 --> 12:03.250
We're a religious charity.

12:03.250 --> 12:05.880
Our donors are very concerned
by the disturbing accounts

12:05.880 --> 12:07.670
of the Harper Avery abuse.

12:07.670 --> 12:09.380
I don't get it -- so, they just
take it out on the boy?

12:09.380 --> 12:12.420
I mean, seriously?
Angels of Humanity, my ass.

12:12.420 --> 12:14.250
-I beg your pardon?
-It's not our decision.

12:14.250 --> 12:16.420
This came from the executive
director and our board.

12:16.420 --> 12:18.000
They want us to take him
to another hospital.

12:18.000 --> 12:19.460
Harper Avery
is not even here!

12:19.460 --> 12:20.880
He's not even alive.

12:20.880 --> 12:22.250
And we completely understand

12:22.250 --> 12:23.380
that you don't want
to be associated

12:23.380 --> 12:26.120
with the Avery name --
neither do we --

12:26.120 --> 12:28.420
but you won't find a better
surgeon than Jackson Avery

12:28.420 --> 12:29.670
to help Diego.

12:29.670 --> 12:32.290
He's stuck with the name,
and so are you.

12:32.290 --> 12:33.960
Our organization
won't pay for the surgery.

12:33.960 --> 12:35.120
There's nothing
we can do.

12:35.120 --> 12:37.500
There is.
Because we can do it pro bono.

12:37.500 --> 12:41.080
And at least Diego
has a shot at survival.

12:41.080 --> 12:44.250
We'll book an O.R.

12:44.250 --> 12:45.750
[ Hushed voice ]
Thank you.

12:45.750 --> 12:48.620
I think Harper Avery's
caused enough casualties.

12:48.620 --> 12:50.080
[ Sarcastically ]
This is such a fun day!

12:53.500 --> 12:54.790
-Excuse me. Can you tell me --
-No comment.

12:54.790 --> 12:56.290
No comment?
Aren't you a doctor?

12:56.290 --> 12:57.750
No comment at all.

12:57.750 --> 12:58.710
This is an E.R., right?

12:58.710 --> 12:59.670
I need someone
to look at my son.

12:59.670 --> 13:00.920
Milo!

13:00.920 --> 13:02.500
Hi.
Hi, how can I help?

13:02.500 --> 13:04.290
We think we might have
swallowed a chew toy.

13:04.290 --> 13:05.420
Say hi, Milo.

13:05.420 --> 13:07.920
[ Whistling noise ]

13:07.920 --> 13:09.460
Good diagnosis. Yeah.

13:09.460 --> 13:10.880
I think it might be lodged
in the epiglotis.

13:10.880 --> 13:12.460
Should we go to trauma one?

13:12.460 --> 13:14.210
Which is where?

13:14.210 --> 13:16.080
I'm so turned around.
It all looks different now.

13:16.080 --> 13:17.380
I used to be
a nurse here.

13:17.380 --> 13:18.750
Another lifetime.

13:18.750 --> 13:20.120
Olivia Jankovic.

13:20.120 --> 13:21.250
Oh, okay.
Well, welcome back.

13:21.250 --> 13:22.620
Trauma one
is right here.

13:22.620 --> 13:24.880
[ Whistle continues ]

13:26.290 --> 13:27.790
[ Baby talking ] Yeah,
we're gonna see Dr. Karev.

13:27.790 --> 13:28.880
That's right.

13:28.880 --> 13:30.170
[ Normal voice ] Hi.

13:30.170 --> 13:31.290
We're here to see
Dr. Karev.

13:31.290 --> 13:32.380
Wellness baby check?

13:32.380 --> 13:33.790
Hunt.

13:33.790 --> 13:34.920
Fill out the first page.

13:34.920 --> 13:38.460
Yeah, I work here.
I'm the head of trauma?

13:38.460 --> 13:41.250
Well, that baby doesn't.

13:41.250 --> 13:42.290
Fill out the form,

13:42.290 --> 13:44.290
and have a seat
until we call you.

13:44.290 --> 13:45.120
Mm.

13:49.500 --> 13:50.540
Did you like her?

13:50.540 --> 13:52.420
I didn't.

13:52.420 --> 13:54.380
[ Groans ] Okay.

13:54.380 --> 13:55.500
[ Coughing ]

14:01.000 --> 14:02.170
You mind
covering your mouth,

14:02.170 --> 14:05.670
or get a mask
from the nurse?

14:05.670 --> 14:07.540
Oh, they said --
they said I could be here.

14:09.620 --> 14:12.000
I'm Betty.

14:12.000 --> 14:13.830
I'm Leo's mom.

14:16.580 --> 14:18.620
Do you know how long
it's been down there?

14:18.620 --> 14:19.620
About an hour.

14:19.620 --> 14:21.000
[ Whistling noise ]

14:21.000 --> 14:22.330
We were having dinner
at my parents',

14:22.330 --> 14:25.080
and my dad started
talking politics, so...

14:25.080 --> 14:26.790
maybe he was looking for
an easy way out.

14:26.790 --> 14:28.250
Uh...

14:28.250 --> 14:29.920
It's a joke, Skippy.

14:29.920 --> 14:31.620
[ Laughs nervously ]

14:31.620 --> 14:33.580
I see we're still getting
the interns straight from Mensa.

14:33.580 --> 14:35.250
[ Laughs ]

14:35.250 --> 14:37.960
Okay, so, the whistle
isn't compromising his airway,

14:37.960 --> 14:40.290
but I'd still like to get some
X-rays to pinpoint the location.

14:40.290 --> 14:42.040
Okay.
I swear to God,

14:42.040 --> 14:43.830
this kid will stick
anything in his mouth.

14:43.830 --> 14:45.580
[ Whistling noise ]
Dude, careful.

14:45.580 --> 14:47.040
Times have changed.

14:47.040 --> 14:48.670
No whistlin'
at the ladies.

14:48.670 --> 14:50.540
[ Chuckles ]

14:50.540 --> 14:52.170
So, this
Harper Avery stuff --

14:52.170 --> 14:53.920
Ugh, nightmare.

14:53.920 --> 14:55.330
I can't say
I'm surprised.

14:55.330 --> 14:57.000
When I was here, you wouldn't
believe the pig doctors

14:57.000 --> 14:58.620
we had to
put up with.

14:58.620 --> 15:01.580
So...

15:01.580 --> 15:04.290
what are we
looking at?

15:04.290 --> 15:06.210
[ Laughs ]

15:06.210 --> 15:07.620
Alex Karev.

15:09.460 --> 15:10.710
Perfect.

15:10.710 --> 15:12.040
Olivia.

15:12.040 --> 15:14.290
You two
know each other?

15:14.290 --> 15:15.880
Is he still
giving nurses syphilis,

15:15.880 --> 15:17.210
or has he moved on
to gonorrhea?

15:17.210 --> 15:21.210
♪♪

15:31.960 --> 15:34.830
Do you want to
hold him?

15:34.830 --> 15:35.790
No. I better not.

15:39.000 --> 15:41.210
Why are we
in a hospital?

15:41.210 --> 15:43.000
Is he really sick?
No, no, no. No, no.

15:43.000 --> 15:45.040
I work here, and these doctors
are my friends,

15:45.040 --> 15:46.080
and I trust them.

15:46.080 --> 15:47.460
Oh. That's cool.

15:47.460 --> 15:48.250
That's...

15:50.500 --> 15:51.750
Hey.

15:51.750 --> 15:52.750
I thought you'd be done
by now.

15:52.750 --> 15:53.960
Yeah, Karev's tied up
in the E.R.

15:53.960 --> 15:54.830
and we're just
sitting here --

15:54.830 --> 15:56.040
[ Hushed voice ]
Is this how we treat patients?

15:56.040 --> 15:57.620
'Cause it is horrible.

15:57.620 --> 15:59.580
Well, I guess
the mom flaked.

15:59.580 --> 16:00.880
You didn't have to worry
about that.

16:00.880 --> 16:02.170
[ Clears throat loudly ]

16:02.170 --> 16:04.920
Dr. Shepherd, this is Betty,
uh, Leo's mom.

16:04.920 --> 16:07.380
Oh!
Betty, goodness. Hi.

16:07.380 --> 16:08.500
It's nice
to meet you.

16:08.500 --> 16:10.210
Hi.

16:10.210 --> 16:11.330
Ahh.

16:11.330 --> 16:16.500
♪♪

16:16.500 --> 16:18.500
So...peds surgery?

16:18.500 --> 16:20.000
What happened
to plastics?

16:20.000 --> 16:21.750
Lucky for you,
I dropped it.

16:21.750 --> 16:23.830
Okay, bud, when you
breathe or swallow,

16:23.830 --> 16:24.710
does that feel
uncomfortable?

16:24.710 --> 16:25.790
[ Whistling noise ]

16:25.790 --> 16:28.040
So, you still in Seattle?

16:28.040 --> 16:29.380
God, no.
Got the hell out.

16:29.380 --> 16:31.210
Sacramento.
Met my husband.

16:31.210 --> 16:33.540
He's intelligent,
kind, faithful --

16:33.540 --> 16:36.290
not your crowd
at all.

16:36.290 --> 16:38.620
Okay. Well, it looks like
it's lodged in his bronchus.

16:38.620 --> 16:39.500
Go ahead with X-rays.

16:42.710 --> 16:43.500
What was that about?

16:43.500 --> 16:44.750
Nothing.

16:44.750 --> 16:46.120
Get chest
and abdominal films.

16:46.120 --> 16:47.540
Keep an eye on
his pulse-ox.

16:47.540 --> 16:48.790
Alex, wait.

16:48.790 --> 16:50.960
If you want to do
a cheaper place, that's fine.

16:50.960 --> 16:52.750
We can give Kepner
whatever budget we want.

16:52.750 --> 16:53.830
Jo, can we just
drop it?

16:53.830 --> 16:55.580
Alex, it's a stupid
wedding budget.

16:55.580 --> 16:58.040
How hard is it to
give me a number?

16:58.040 --> 17:00.210
So, is someone gonna
come get us, or...?

17:00.210 --> 17:02.580
Yeah. We're gonna
bring him up right now.

17:02.580 --> 17:04.540
Okay.

17:04.540 --> 17:06.330
Are you
and Karev engaged?

17:06.330 --> 17:08.290
Yeah.

17:08.290 --> 17:09.500
Best of luck with that.

17:15.080 --> 17:16.080
Thank you
for doing this.

17:16.080 --> 17:17.420
Oh, my gosh,
it is a treat.

17:17.420 --> 17:20.210
I rarely get to treat healthy
babies, and this is one.

17:20.210 --> 17:21.620
Doesn't that
bother him?

17:21.620 --> 17:23.170
No, no, no.
He's just reacting to the light.

17:23.170 --> 17:25.580
It's a good thing.

17:25.580 --> 17:28.210
You can come in closer
if you want. He's your...

17:28.210 --> 17:32.290
All right. Let's flex and rotate
to check for hip dysplasia.

17:32.290 --> 17:33.290
[ Leo coos ]

17:33.290 --> 17:34.960
[ Baby talking ]
Oh, yeah!

17:34.960 --> 17:36.330
[ Normal voice ]
He's super strong and limber.

17:36.330 --> 17:37.750
[ Laughs ]

17:37.750 --> 17:38.750
He's a future Olympian!

17:38.750 --> 17:41.880
Look at those strong,
powerful legs.

17:41.880 --> 17:43.500
He gets those from me.

17:43.500 --> 17:45.540
I was the fastest kid
on my soccer team.

17:45.540 --> 17:47.620
Coach called me
"Lightning Bolt Betty."

17:47.620 --> 17:49.750
[ Leo fussing ]

17:49.750 --> 17:51.500
Okay, this is my
least favorite part,

17:51.500 --> 17:54.170
but Leo needs this, and I
promise I'll be super fast.

17:58.380 --> 18:00.170
You know, I get really squeamish
around needles, too.

18:00.170 --> 18:03.120
You want to
step outside with me?

18:03.120 --> 18:04.460
[ Baby talking ] Hi.

18:04.460 --> 18:05.880
[ Normal voice ] All right,
let's make it really quick,

18:05.880 --> 18:07.000
really quick, really quick,
really quick.

18:07.000 --> 18:08.040
A-a-and...

18:08.040 --> 18:10.460
So stupid.

18:10.460 --> 18:11.460
What is?

18:11.460 --> 18:13.040
I got a dress.

18:13.040 --> 18:16.380
Like, I went out and got
a new dress for this.

18:16.380 --> 18:19.380
Like Leo would know if I'm
wearing a dress or not.

18:19.380 --> 18:20.830
This guy's
a friggin' doctor.

18:20.830 --> 18:22.080
What can I do for him?

18:24.670 --> 18:26.250
You hungry?

18:26.250 --> 18:28.210
I skipped breakfast.
I'm dying.

18:28.210 --> 18:29.250
Come on.
it's on me.

18:29.250 --> 18:31.290
[ Leo fussing ]

18:31.290 --> 18:32.920
[ Leo cooing ]

18:40.290 --> 18:41.670
Syph Nurse.

18:41.670 --> 18:43.080
Sorry?

18:43.080 --> 18:45.540
That's what
they called me --

18:45.540 --> 18:48.120
"Syph Nurse."

18:48.120 --> 18:51.580
It was all over
the hospital.

18:51.580 --> 18:53.290
A lot of laughs.

18:53.290 --> 18:54.880
And I got it from Karev,
but nobody was calling him

18:54.880 --> 18:55.880
"Syph Doc."

18:55.880 --> 18:57.880
I'm sorry.
That's awful.

18:57.880 --> 18:59.420
Oh, please.
I'm over it.

18:59.420 --> 19:04.040
I should shut up, but you
seem pretty great and, just...

19:04.040 --> 19:05.380
You know he cheated
on his first wife?

19:05.380 --> 19:07.040
Um...
[ Levi clears throat ]

19:07.040 --> 19:08.830
Who told you that?
-Nobody.

19:08.830 --> 19:10.170
He cheated with me.

19:10.170 --> 19:12.540
So, I kind of lost the moral
high ground on that one.

19:12.540 --> 19:15.210
And to be fair,
they weren't married yet,

19:15.210 --> 19:18.210
so it's slightly less horrible
on his part.

19:18.210 --> 19:20.920
Well, I appreciate that,
I guess.

19:20.920 --> 19:24.420
But that was a long time ago.
People change.

19:24.420 --> 19:26.290
You're right.
Absolutely.

19:26.290 --> 19:29.080
Of course, it couldn't hurt
to get tested.

19:29.080 --> 19:31.540
Okay.
I reviewed his X-rays.

19:31.540 --> 19:33.920
The whistle is lodged
in his right mainstem bronchus.

19:33.920 --> 19:36.540
I'd like to get it out of there
before it causes a bronchospasm.

19:36.540 --> 19:37.790
You good with that?

19:37.790 --> 19:38.830
You're the doctor.

19:43.790 --> 19:47.040
Jackson: And after we dissect
the internal maxillary artery,

19:47.040 --> 19:49.460
we'll continue to remove
the tumor burden

19:49.460 --> 19:52.540
and prevent compromise
to the orbital floor.

19:52.540 --> 19:54.540
I still think we should take
the whole tumor out.

19:54.540 --> 19:55.500
We're past that.

19:55.500 --> 19:57.170
But why?

19:57.170 --> 20:00.380
Diego is going to have to come
back here time and time again,

20:00.380 --> 20:03.330
and risk bleeding out
every single time.

20:03.330 --> 20:05.170
We could just do
a bone graft right now.

20:05.170 --> 20:06.670
-It's too risky.
-"Risky"?

20:06.670 --> 20:08.080
Jackson,
everything is risky.

20:08.080 --> 20:09.790
Surgery is risky.

20:09.790 --> 20:12.620
Not too long ago,
you did a throat transplant.

20:12.620 --> 20:13.830
Where's that guy?

20:13.830 --> 20:15.830
That's the guy
Diego needs today.

20:15.830 --> 20:17.080
Yeah, well,
it's not that simple.

20:17.080 --> 20:19.000
Yeah, it is that simple.
It should be that simple --

20:19.000 --> 20:20.620
if you weren't so concerned
with getting bad press.

20:20.620 --> 20:21.670
I'm not!

20:26.000 --> 20:27.620
Fine. Maybe I am,
all right?

20:27.620 --> 20:29.380
That's only 'cause I'm concerned
about the foundation.

20:29.380 --> 20:32.420
But why are you even thinking
about that right now?

20:32.420 --> 20:35.500
I'm sure Katie Simmons
isn't thinking about that.

20:35.500 --> 20:36.750
-Who?
-Katie Simmons.

20:36.750 --> 20:38.170
She was all over the news
this morning.

20:38.170 --> 20:40.170
She was a 3rd-year neuro.

20:40.170 --> 20:42.710
She was harassed,
assaulted, paid off.

20:42.710 --> 20:44.080
She dropped out
of the program.

20:44.080 --> 20:45.500
She's a waitress now.

20:45.500 --> 20:47.670
Do you think she's thinking
about the foundation, Hellmouth?

20:47.670 --> 20:49.250
Preach.

20:49.250 --> 20:51.380
All right, I'm not trying
to diminish the trauma

20:51.380 --> 20:53.080
experienced by these victims,
all right?

20:53.080 --> 20:54.250
If you take
the foundation down,

20:54.250 --> 20:56.790
that's 72 hospitals
that go down with it.

20:56.790 --> 21:00.080
Every single person in this
hospital -- multiply that by 72.

21:00.080 --> 21:04.210
We're talking about thousands
of jobs, thousands of families.

21:04.210 --> 21:05.380
You know, of all people,
I really thought

21:05.380 --> 21:06.460
you would understand.

21:06.460 --> 21:08.750
Understand what?

21:08.750 --> 21:11.000
We're not exactly raised
by people who were easy.

21:11.000 --> 21:12.670
No. You don't get
to do that.

21:12.670 --> 21:15.330
You don't get to compare your
grandfather and my mother.

21:15.330 --> 21:17.540
My mother had to fight
tooth and nail

21:17.540 --> 21:19.620
for every inch of ground
she gained.

21:19.620 --> 21:22.540
Harper Avery
had everything...

21:22.540 --> 21:25.210
except decency.

21:25.210 --> 21:26.790
We're ready. Let me know
when the O.R. is prepped.

21:26.790 --> 21:31.420
♪♪

21:38.170 --> 21:39.420
Turn the scope
to the right.

21:39.420 --> 21:41.120
Nope, your other right.

21:41.120 --> 21:42.120
Yes...

21:42.120 --> 21:45.330
Just looking for
the whistle.

21:45.330 --> 21:46.750
And I see it.

21:46.750 --> 21:48.750
Secure the object
with your forceps.

21:48.750 --> 21:50.880
Do me a favor -- try not to
perforate the airway.

21:50.880 --> 21:52.170
His mom hates me enough
as it is.

21:52.170 --> 21:53.920
Well, you did
give her syphilis.

21:53.920 --> 21:55.460
Olivia has a right
to be pissed.

21:55.460 --> 21:56.710
I was an idiot back then.

21:56.710 --> 21:57.880
They used to call me
"Evilspawn."

21:57.880 --> 21:59.420
[ Laughs ]
Evilspawn?

21:59.420 --> 22:01.710
Okay, last time I complain
about "Glasses."

22:01.710 --> 22:04.040
Shut up, Schmitt.
All right.

22:04.040 --> 22:08.000
Angle the tip down and rotate
your wrist 90 degrees clockwise.

22:08.000 --> 22:10.830
If anything, I think I was
more troubled by the cheating

22:10.830 --> 22:13.290
on your first wife.

22:13.290 --> 22:14.790
We've known
each other forever.

22:14.790 --> 22:16.290
Do you really think
I'm like that?

22:16.290 --> 22:17.960
No. But I think you're
being really weird

22:17.960 --> 22:19.670
about setting a date.

22:19.670 --> 22:21.790
Bingo!
I got the whistle.

22:21.790 --> 22:23.880
How cool is that?

22:23.880 --> 22:25.500
Owen:
[ Baby talking ] Okay.

22:25.500 --> 22:28.710
Bye.

22:28.710 --> 22:30.880
[ Sighs ]
Thanks for earlier.
I know you're busy.

22:30.880 --> 22:32.330
No, no, I'm not.

22:32.330 --> 22:33.960
Actually, I was home
with Sofia all morning.

22:33.960 --> 22:34.960
I had to
push some things.

22:34.960 --> 22:37.620
Is Sofia okay?
Yeah.

22:37.620 --> 22:38.830
No.
No.

22:38.830 --> 22:40.250
She's sad,
all the time.

22:40.250 --> 22:42.000
Do you want to
bring her over?

22:42.000 --> 22:43.460
She might get a kick out of
playing with Leo.

22:43.460 --> 22:44.790
Kids love babies.

22:44.790 --> 22:46.210
Yes! Thank you!

22:46.210 --> 22:48.790
That is a normal
human reaction!

22:48.790 --> 22:50.080
Thank you!
Thank you!

22:57.920 --> 22:59.710
You seriously
can't beat this truck.

22:59.710 --> 23:03.750
It's so much better
than the food inside.

23:03.750 --> 23:06.460
Yeah.
It's pretty good.

23:06.460 --> 23:07.750
So...

23:10.750 --> 23:13.960
...how long have you
been using?

23:13.960 --> 23:16.000
I don't know where
you got that idea.

23:16.000 --> 23:20.830
I guess from the itching
and the bruising on your arms,

23:20.830 --> 23:23.830
the constricted pupils.

23:23.830 --> 23:25.460
I have allergies.

23:25.460 --> 23:27.880
Ah. Yeah.

23:27.880 --> 23:29.000
I had "allergies," too.

23:31.580 --> 23:32.380
For a long time.

23:36.750 --> 23:39.420
I was never
into drugs.

23:39.420 --> 23:42.000
I never smoked weed.

23:42.000 --> 23:44.580
I didn't hang out
with the stoners.

23:44.580 --> 23:46.830
I thought they were losers.
[ Laughs ]

23:46.830 --> 23:48.620
Whoops.

23:48.620 --> 23:49.670
You were a jock?

23:49.670 --> 23:51.540
Soccer.

