you did it.

37:06.710 --> 37:09.670
You wanted to compete.
I get it.

37:09.670 --> 37:10.710
Thank you.

37:15.080 --> 37:17.420
You were very
impressive today.

37:17.420 --> 37:19.000
Was I?
It was hot.

37:19.000 --> 37:21.250
Still gonna be hot
if I go broke?

37:21.250 --> 37:23.250
Are you going broke
for noble reasons?

37:23.250 --> 37:24.290
Maybe.

37:24.290 --> 37:25.380
Yep, still hot.

37:31.120 --> 37:32.580
Cooking?

37:32.580 --> 37:33.710
Oh, I'm full
of surprises.

37:33.710 --> 37:35.540
[ Chuckles ]

37:35.540 --> 37:37.790
Risotto.

37:37.790 --> 37:38.830
Salmon.

37:42.330 --> 37:44.620
[ Breathes deeply ]

37:44.620 --> 37:47.250
It was a stupid idea,
anyway.

37:47.250 --> 37:49.830
She probably thought
I was some nut job --

37:49.830 --> 37:54.080
"Hey, we just met.
Why don't you move in with me?"

37:54.080 --> 37:55.120
Amelia...

37:57.540 --> 37:58.790
...she's here.

37:58.790 --> 37:59.830
She showed.

38:02.830 --> 38:05.880
Oh, God.
Um...

38:05.880 --> 38:07.120
I'm her Ollie.

38:15.460 --> 38:16.250
Okay.

38:19.380 --> 38:22.580
Well, if this is gonna work,
there need to be ground rules.

38:22.580 --> 38:24.620
First off,
you text your family -- tonight.

38:24.620 --> 38:26.040
You let them know
that you're safe

38:26.040 --> 38:28.170
and that you're
off the streets.

38:28.170 --> 38:30.830
You cannot do drugs at all,
okay?

38:30.830 --> 38:32.080
That is a non-starter.

38:32.080 --> 38:33.460
I can give you
a prescription

38:33.460 --> 38:35.620
to take the edge off your
withdrawal, but that's all.

38:35.620 --> 38:37.500
And you have to come
with me to meetings.

38:37.500 --> 38:40.250
She's so bossy.

38:40.250 --> 38:42.880
Oh, yeah.
[ Chuckles ]

38:42.880 --> 38:46.620
Meredith:
We define ourselves
by our actions.

38:46.620 --> 38:48.290
Who's ready
to go home?

38:48.290 --> 38:51.040
But it doesn't mean we have
to live by that definition.

38:51.040 --> 38:54.620
♪♪

38:54.620 --> 38:56.710
We can change our own story.

38:56.710 --> 39:01.290
♪♪

39:01.290 --> 39:02.790
Robbins?

39:02.790 --> 39:04.120
I'm glad I caught you.

39:04.120 --> 39:05.620
You're close
with DeLuca, right?

39:05.620 --> 39:08.830
Close? Well, we were roommates,
so, yeah, okay.

39:08.830 --> 39:11.460
Okay.
So, I'm worried about him.

39:11.460 --> 39:13.210
Maggie brought him home
about a week ago,

39:13.210 --> 39:15.170
and he hasn't gotten off
the couch since.

39:15.170 --> 39:16.920
I mean, I'm literally gonna have
to put it out on the sidewalk

39:16.920 --> 39:18.460
when he leaves.
Ooh, yikes.

39:18.460 --> 39:21.170
Yeah. So, I was hoping you could
talk to him, maybe.

39:21.170 --> 39:23.290
We can refuse to accept the way
people define us.

39:23.290 --> 39:25.290
I don't that I'm
the person for the job,

39:25.290 --> 39:27.380
but I think I do know
the person you should talk to.

39:28.750 --> 39:33.880
We can work like hell
to escape a bad reputation...

39:33.880 --> 39:35.250
[ Sighs ]

39:35.250 --> 39:37.380
...only to wonder
if we succeeded.

39:37.380 --> 39:40.170
Okay, we're having it out
right now.

39:40.170 --> 39:42.210
Oh, come on. You're seriously
gonna listen to

39:42.210 --> 39:44.580
some nurse I slept with
when I was a stupid intern?

39:44.580 --> 39:47.210
No! I'm talking about
your psycho mood swings

39:47.210 --> 39:48.960
and treating me
like crap all day.

39:48.960 --> 39:51.750
I won't do weirdness
and silence and anger, Alex.

39:51.750 --> 39:52.920
I can't do that again.

39:52.920 --> 39:54.500
It's not what you think.

39:54.500 --> 39:56.540
It started when I asked you
to check your bank account.

39:56.540 --> 39:58.080
Is it money?

39:58.080 --> 39:59.420
Are we really fighting
about money?

39:59.420 --> 40:01.170
Because that is such
a cliché.

40:01.170 --> 40:02.960
I grew up in
my fricking car, Alex.

40:02.960 --> 40:05.380
Do you think I care if
you're having money problems?

40:05.380 --> 40:06.540
It's not.

40:06.540 --> 40:08.210
I have money --

40:08.210 --> 40:10.460
way too much money.

40:10.460 --> 40:12.330
I haven't checked this account
in over a year,

40:12.330 --> 40:14.880
and all of a sudden,
my balance is crazy high.

40:14.880 --> 40:15.880
Okay.

40:15.880 --> 40:17.960
It's my mom.

40:17.960 --> 40:19.580
I send her money
for rent and food,

40:19.580 --> 40:22.040
and she hasn't been
cashing the checks.

40:22.040 --> 40:23.210
Which means
she's dead

40:23.210 --> 40:25.540
or walking the streets
half-naked

40:25.540 --> 40:28.380
or throwing garbage
at people.

40:28.380 --> 40:29.880
[ Breathes deeply ]

40:29.880 --> 40:31.920
I'm out here living my life,
and I'm just throwing money

40:31.920 --> 40:33.330
at a problem without
paying attention.

40:35.040 --> 40:36.880
I don't know.

40:36.880 --> 40:39.380
Maybe I haven't really
changed that much.

40:39.380 --> 40:40.960
No.
That's not true.

40:40.960 --> 40:43.670
You know that
that's not true.

40:43.670 --> 40:46.830
It can be hard to shake
the mistakes of the past.

40:46.830 --> 40:48.920
♪♪

40:48.920 --> 40:52.120
They'll always come back
to haunt us.

40:52.120 --> 40:53.880
Man:
Dr. Miranda Bailey?

40:53.880 --> 40:55.500
I told y'all,
I have no comment

40:55.500 --> 40:56.830
about the ongoing
Harper Avery --

40:56.830 --> 40:59.460
Sanjay Roy.
I'm representing a client

40:59.460 --> 41:00.920
in a wrongful-termination
suit.

41:00.920 --> 41:02.170
Wrongful --

41:02.170 --> 41:04.750
Well, who was
wrongfully terminated?

41:04.750 --> 41:07.250
My client is
Dr. Vikram Roy.

41:07.250 --> 41:08.960
Roy?

41:08.960 --> 41:10.460
Is this your brother?

41:10.460 --> 41:12.830
Dr. Roy was under your employ
when he was fed

41:12.830 --> 41:14.960
psychotropic
marijuana cookies

41:14.960 --> 41:17.120
by a superior
in the workplace.

41:17.120 --> 41:18.960
This is just a courtesy visit,
to inform you

41:18.960 --> 41:21.460
we'll we suing for restitution
of employment

41:21.460 --> 41:24.420
as well as unspecified damages
for pain and suffering.

41:24.420 --> 41:27.580
I have weekend plans, but I'm
happy to start back on Monday.

41:27.580 --> 41:30.620
♪ Lifting from the ground ♪

41:30.620 --> 41:35.040
♪ We go ♪

41:35.040 --> 41:36.420
♪ Never coming down ♪

41:36.420 --> 41:39.290
But one thing we never do --

41:39.290 --> 41:42.920
we don't stop.
We don't quit.

41:42.920 --> 41:44.460
♪ I'll take you there ♪

41:44.460 --> 41:47.080
Meredith:
Hey, Garfunkel...

41:47.080 --> 41:48.920
[ Groans ]
Leave me alone.

41:48.920 --> 41:50.460
I have something
for you.

41:50.460 --> 41:52.290
We get up
and rejoin the fight.

41:52.290 --> 41:53.710
Andrew,
this is disgusting.

41:53.710 --> 41:54.830
Oh, no, no, no.
Why did --

41:54.830 --> 41:55.960
No, no, no, no.
Why did --

41:55.960 --> 41:57.210
No, come on.

41:57.210 --> 42:00.790
[ Both yelling in Italian ]

42:00.790 --> 42:03.000
Please, God, don't let him
forget his guitar.

42:03.000 --> 42:05.040
[ Yelling continues ]

42:05.040 --> 42:11.920
♪♪
